"One day I'll be one of the 10, just like daddy!"
"I won't mind it being The magnificent 11!" Borgar The Wall said between laughs.
"Who's your daddy, my dear?" Stein The Slaughterer asked the excited girl.
"Gunnar The Brave!" Helena replied effusively. https://t.co/Jn85mPStsJ

The big battle was over, and the magnificent 10 all returned without a single scratch. The entire clan joyfully celebrated their return.
"One day, I'll be one of them. Just like daddy!" Helena's excitement was so effusive that it captured the attention of some of the champions. https://t.co/8V0N0Iaf1J

"I'm a warrior, not a damsel." Young Helena kept saying as her mother prepared her for the big celebration.
"It doesn't matter if it's in a war or a wedding, jubilance or disaster. My daughter will always flaunt the most beautiful braid in front of everyone," Her mother replied. https://t.co/y4WL7Zn09S

"I wanna become a warrior just like daddy!" The young Helena repeated every time Gunnar told one of his stories. Between laughs and jokes, Gunnar had no idea how strong her resolve was. https://t.co/6iA75xcCqd

When the clan knew that the first son of the champion was a girl, they were all disappointed, but Gunnar The Brave didn't feel the same. 
"I'll name you Helena, my brightest light,"
For the first time in his life, tears were coming down Gunnar's eyes, and they were tears of joy. https://t.co/j8FIOGf8ll
